What you guys may be facing is that 2 of these seaqson 15 torrents, (the 2 newest, have the same ID number. Utorrent and all bittorrent will not allow 2 torrents with the same ID number even if the other info and title are different.

I went through my download history to find the 2 that had the same ID number, but when I went back to TPB, the one duplicate was already corrected by the uploader. 
This ONLY happens when someone cuts and pastes someone else's upload and then just adds there user name to the end to make the name different.

NOTE:
THIS IS A REAL TORRENT, BUT IS NOT THE TORRENT WITH A DUPLICATE.

THIS IS the EXAMPLE:

http://thepiratebay.org/torrent/6741735/South_park_season_15_episode_8_Last_of_the_meehecans_[WOBF]

See the 6741735 number in the torrent above, if this number is repeated in another torrent's URL, You will run into a problem where the torrent won't go into your que.
All Bit torrent software, weather it is uTorrent or Transmission or whatever, ONLY looks at that number to know one torrent form another. Even if the names are totally different and even if the movie or show isn't the same. your Bit torrent client will act as if your re-adding a torrent. This was the problem I encountered. I doubt anyones utorrent or whatever they use is messed up. I wanted to share this to help anyone else that finds this problem.AND....

Go try to download the title again. Make sure you re-enter SOUTH PARK key word again like your searching for the first time again. This will make sure you get sent to the updated List of SOUTH PARK downloads.

Hope this helps anyone that had the same symptoms I mentioned above. Cheers!
